{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XTMSB51anBCfRx3H5DwZHs","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Codebase Exploration Report: Temper Ingestion Module\n\n### 1. **Framework & Language**\n- **Framework**: Spring Boot (Java)\n- **Build Tool**: Maven\n- **Key Dependencies**:\n  - Spring Data JPA (Hibernate)\n  - Spring WebFlux (reactive)\n  - Redisson (Redis client)\n  - Micrometer (metrics)\n  - Lombok (annotations)\n\n### 2. **Key File Locations**\n\n| Component | Path |\n|-----------|------|\n| **EntityController** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/controller/EntityController.java` |\n| **EntityService (Interface)** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/EntityService.java` |\n| **EntityServiceImpl** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/EntityServiceImpl.java` |\n| **PolicyController** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/controller/PolicyController.java` |\n| **PolicyReprocessJob** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/job/PolicyReprocessJob.java` |\n| **PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/job/event/PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent.java` |\n| **EntityRepository** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/repository/EntityRepository.java` |\n| **Entity Model** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/entity/Entity.java` |\n| **PolicyReprocessAsyncConfig** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/config/PolicyReprocessAsyncConfig.java` |\n\n### 3. **EntityController - Existing Endpoints**\n\n**Class**: `@RestController @RequestMapping(\"/api/v1/entities\")`\n\n**Endpoints**:\n1. `POST /api/v1/entities/query` - Query failed entities\n   - Request: `EntityQueryDTO` (stage, code, pageNum, pageSize, sortKey, sortOrder)\n   - Response: `ResultDTO<Pagination<Entity>>`\n   \n2. `GET /api/v1/entities/{id}` - Get entity by ID\n   - Response: `Entity`\n   \n3. `GET /api/v1/entities/{id}/display-status` - Get entity display status\n   - Response: `ResultDTO<EntityStateDisplayDTO>`\n   - Maps `ReprocessState` to display status strings: \"init\", \"running\", \"enforced\", \"failed\"\n\n**Key Constraint** (from code comment):\n> \"This controller must NOT reference repository classes directly. All data access must go through an @Service layer class.\"\n\n### 4. **EntityService Interface Methods**\n\nKey methods relevant to reprocessing:\n```java\nEntity getById(Long id);\nvoid save(Entity entity);\nvoid saveBatch(Collection<Entity> entityList);\nPagination<Entity> queryFailedEntities(EntityQueryDTO req);\nboolean isProcessingFinished(Long entityId);\nboolean updateProcessingState(Entity fresh);\n\n// Reprocess-specific methods\nMarkForReprocessResult markAllForReprocess();\nList<Long> findTopNIdsByReprocessState(ReprocessState state, int limit);\nEntityProcessLockInfo findProcessLockInfoById(Long id);\nboolean claimInitEntityForReprocess(Long id);\nboolean updateReprocessStateById(Long id, ReprocessState state);\n```\n\n### 5. **Policy Reprocess Flow Architecture**\n\n#### **Flow Diagram**:\n```\n1. PolicyController.applyExistingEntities() \n   └─> EntityService.markAllForReprocess()\n       └─> Batch updates entities to ReprocessState.INIT\n       └─> Returns MarkForReprocessResult\n   \n2. publishEvent(PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent)\n   └─> Triggers PolicyReprocessJob.onPolicyReprocessRequested()\n   \n3. PolicyReprocessJob (background job)\n   ├─ Scheduled: Every 30 seconds (configurable)\n   ├─ Event-driven: When PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent fires\n   └─> Workflow per entity:\n       1. Acquire distributed scan lock (Redis)\n       2. Drain INIT entities in batches\n       3. For each entity:\n          a. Acquire processLock (Redis, per entity)\n          b. Claim entity (INIT → RUNNING, atomic DB update)\n          c. Load full entity\n          d. Reset processing state\n          e. Run state machine\n          f. Update final reprocessState (SUCCESS|FAILED)\n```\n\n#### **ReprocessState Enum Values**:\n- `NONE` - Default, no reprocessing initiated\n- `INIT` - Marked for reprocessing, waiting to be claimed\n- `RUNNING` - Actively being reprocessed\n- `SUCCESS` - Reprocessing completed successfully (ENFORCED stage + code 0)\n- `FAILED` - Reprocessing failed\n\n### 6. **PolicyController - Reprocess Endpoint**\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /api/v1/policy/apply-existing-entities`\n\n**Flow**:\n```java\n1. Calls entityService.markAllForReprocess()\n   - Batches entities that need reprocessing\n   - Updates reprocessState to INIT\n   - Returns MarkForReprocessResult with counts\n\n2. On success (count > 0):\n   - Publishes PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent\n   - Event includes: markedCount and triggerSource=\"api\"\n\n3. Response Structure:\n   ResultDTO<MarkForReprocessResponse> {\n     markedCount: int,\n     failedBatches: int,\n     failedCount: int,\n     timeCostMs: long,\n     status: \"SUCCESS\" | \"PARTIAL_SUCCESS\" | \"FAILED\",\n     message: String\n   }\n\n4. Error Handling:\n   - Returns ResultDTO.error() on exceptions\n   - Includes DEFAULT_ERROR_CODE + error message\n```\n\n### 7. **MarkForReprocess Pattern Details**\n\n**MarkForReprocessResult** (internal DTO):\n```java\n@Data @Builder\npublic class MarkForReprocessResult {\n    int updatedCount;          // Entities successfully marked\n    int failedBatches;         // Number of batch failures\n    int failedCount;           // Total entities failed in batches\n}\n```\n\n**MarkForReprocessResponse** (HTTP response):\n```java\n@Data @Builder\npublic class MarkForReprocessResponse {\n    int markedCount;           // Same as updatedCount\n    int failedBatches;\n    int failedCount;\n    long timeCostMs;           // Execution time\n    String status;             // \"FAILED\" | \"PARTIAL_SUCCESS\" | \"SUCCESS\"\n    String message;            // Human-readable message\n}\n```\n\n**Configuration** (in application.yaml):\n```yaml\npolicy:\n  reprocess:\n    mark-init-batch-size: 1000          # Batch size for marking\n    scan-batch-size: 100                # Batch size for scanning\n    max-candidates-per-scan: 1000       # Max entities per scan\n    rate-limit-per-second: 100          # Throttling for downstream\n    scan-interval-ms: 30000             # Scheduled job frequency\n    scan-lock-ttl-seconds: 900          # Distributed lock TTL\n    listener:\n      core-size: 1\n      max-size: 2\n      queue-capacity: 100\n    job:\n      core-size: 8\n      max-size: 16\n      queue-capacity: 32\n```\n\n### 8. **PolicyReprocessJob - Reprocess Processing**\n\n**Trigger Points**:\n1. **Scheduled**: `@Scheduled(fixedDelayString = \"${policy.reprocess.scan-interval-ms:30000}\")`\n2. **Event-Driven**: `@EventListener` on `PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent`\n\n**Key Methods**:\n```java\npublic void scanAndReprocessInitEntities()  // Scheduled trigger\npublic void onPolicyReprocessRequested(PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent event)  // Event trigger\nprivate void triggerScan(String triggerSource)  // Acquires distributed lock\nprivate void drainInitEntities()  // Main processing loop\nprivate void processBatchConcurrently(List<Long> batchIds, ReprocessRateLimiter rateLimiter)\nprivate void reprocessOneEntity(Long entityId, ReprocessRateLimiter rateLimiter)\n```\n\n**Entity Processing Steps** (in `reprocessOneEntity`):\n1. Load lightweight `EntityProcessLockInfo` (projection with id, type, hostId, adapterId, userId, reprocessState)\n2. Verify state is still INIT (may have changed)\n3. Acquire process lock (Redis key based on entity identity)\n4. **Atomic claim**: Update INIT → RUNNING in one DB statement\n5. Load full entity\n6. Reset processing state:\n   - `interrupted = false`\n   - `processingStage = \"PENDING\"`\n   - `processingCode = 0`\n   - `processingResult = \"{}\"`\n   - `errorMessage = \"\"`\n7. Run state machine: `stateMachine.start(requestId, true, fresh)`\n8. Update final state:\n   - If state machine OK and stage=\"ENFORCED\" and code=0 → `ReprocessState.SUCCESS`\n   - Otherwise → `ReprocessState.FAILED`\n9. Release process lock\n\n**Rate Limiting**:\n- Token bucket algorithm implemented in `ReprocessRateLimiter` inner class\n- Configurable via `policy.reprocess.rate-limit-per-second`\n- Prevents overwhelming downstream systems\n\n**Distributed Locking**:\n- **Scan Lock**: Prevents concurrent full scans (Redis key: `POLICY_REPROCESS_SCAN_LOCK_KEY`)\n- **Process Lock**: Per-entity lock to avoid conflicts with normal ingestion flow\n- Lock acquisitions recorded as metrics: `policy_reproc_lock_acquire_total`\n\n### 9. **EntityRepository - Query Patterns**\n\n**Key Custom Queries** (for reprocessing):\n```java\n// Find entities that need marking as INIT\nList<Long> findTopNIdsNeedMarkForReprocess(\n    @Param(\"lastId\") Long lastId,\n    @Param(\"targetState\") ReprocessState targetState,\n    Pageable pageable);\n\n// Batch mark entities for reprocessing\nint markBatchForReprocess(\n    @Param(\"ids\") List<Long> ids,\n    @Param(\"targetState\") ReprocessState targetState);\n\n// Find entities by reprocess state\nList<Long> findTopNIdsByReprocessState(\n    @Param(\"state\") ReprocessState state,\n    Pageable pageable);\n\n// Lightweight projection for lock check\nOptional<EntityProcessLockInfo> findProcessLockInfoById(\n    @Param(\"id\") Long id);\n\n// Atomic claim operation\nint claimInitEntityForReprocess(\n    @Param(\"id\") Long id,\n    @Param(\"updatedAt\") Instant updatedAt);\n\n// Update reprocess state\nint updateReprocessStateById(\n    @Param(\"id\") Long id,\n    @Param(\"state\") ReprocessState state,\n    @Param(\"updatedAt\") Instant updatedAt);\n```\n\n### 10. **Event Publishing Pattern**\n\n**Event Class**:\n```java\npublic class PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent {\n    private final int markedCount;\n    private final String triggerSource;  // \"api\" or \"scheduled\"\n}\n```\n\n**Publishing in PolicyController**:\n```java\nif (count > 0) {\n    eventPublisher.publishEvent(new PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent(count, \"api\"));\n}\n```\n\n**Listening in PolicyReprocessJob**:\n```java\n@Async(\"policyReprocessListenerExecutor\")\n@EventListener\npublic void onPolicyReprocessRequested(PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent event) {\n    triggerScan(\"event\");\n}\n```\n\n### 11. **Response Pattern (ResultDTO)**\n\nUsed throughout ingestion module:\n```java\n// Success response\nResultDTO.success(data)\nResultDTO.success(data, traceId)\n\n// Error response\nResultDTO.error(errorCode, message)\nResultDTO.<Type>builder()\n    .code(ResultDTO.DEFAULT_ERROR_CODE)\n    .errMsg(message)\n    .data(data)\n    .build()\n```\n\n### 12. **Transaction Management**\n\nKey annotations:\n- `@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)` - Used for batch operations to ensure each batch is independent\n- Batch failures don't block subsequent batches\n- `TransactionTemplate` used explicitly in `markAllForReprocess()` for fine-grained control\n\n### 13. **Metrics Recorded**\n\n```java\npolicy_reprocess_mark_init_last_failed_batches  // Gauge\npolicy_reprocess_mark_init_run_seconds          // Timer with tag: result\npolicy_reprocess_scan_lock_consecutive_failures // Gauge\npolicy_reproc_lock_acquire_total                // Counter with tags: lock, result\npolicy_reproc_lock_hold_seconds                 // Timer with tag: lock\npolicy_reprocess_entity_completed_total         // Counter with tag: result\npolicy_reprocess_rate_limiter_wait_total        // Counter\n```\n\n### 14. **Error Handling Patterns**\n\n- **Batch failures**: Logged, tracked, next batch continues\n- **Lock acquisition failures**: Logged, marked as starvation metric, skip trigger\n- **Entity processing failures**: Caught, entity marked as `ReprocessState.FAILED`, loop continues\n- **State machine errors**: Entity marked as `FAILED` via ID update (lightweight operation)\n\n### 15. **Architecture Constraints & Best Practices**\n\n1. **Layered Architecture**: Controllers → Services → Repositories\n2. **No direct repository injection into controllers**\n3. **Distributed locking** for cluster-safe operations\n4. **Projection queries** for lightweight operations (e.g., `EntityProcessLockInfo`)\n5. **Batch processing** with independent transactions per batch\n6. **Rate limiting** to protect downstream systems\n7. **Metrics-driven observability** for all critical paths\n8. **Async processing** for event handling and concurrent reprocessing\n\nThis codebase demonstrates a well-architected policy reprocessing flow with robust error handling, distributed locking, rate limiting, and comprehensive metrics."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"96f50260-dc60-4a75-a501-57c5af917508","uuid":"98b6b4a6-b550-48be-8dbc-5fd6cebe17ca","timestamp":"2026-04-20T08:18:50.900Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion. I need to understand:\n1. Find EntityController and EntityService files (exact paths)\n2. Read their full contents — especially existing endpoints/methods, request/response patterns, annotations, imports\n3. Look at how other \"reprocess\" or \"trigger\" style endpoints are done elsewhere if any\n4. Check what \"policy reprocess flow\" looks like — any existing policy-related service calls, event publishing, queue publishing, etc.\n5. Note the framework (Spring Boot? NestJS? FastAPI? etc.), language, and any relevant patterns (DTOs, response wrappers, error handling)\n\nBe thorough. Report file paths, key class/method signatures, and the patterns used.","agentId":"a37a2071931a01008","agentType"