 For each entity:\n          a. Acquire processLock (Redis, per entity)\n          b. Claim entity (INIT → RUNNING, atomic DB update)\n          c. Load full entity\n          d. Reset processing state\n          e. Run state machine\n          f. Update final reprocessState (SUCCESS|FAILED)\n```\n\n#### **ReprocessState Enum Values**:\n- `NONE` - Default, no reprocessing initiated\n- `INIT` - Marked for reprocessing, waiting to be claimed\n- `RUNNING` - Actively being reprocessed\n- `SUCCESS` - Reprocessing completed successfully (ENFORCED stage + code 0)\n- `FAILED` - Reprocessing failed\n\n### 6. **PolicyController - Reprocess Endpoint**\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /api/v1/policy/apply-existing-entities`\n\n**Flow**:\n```java\n1. Calls entityService.markAllForReprocess()\n   - Batches entities that need reprocessing\n   - Updates reprocessState to INIT\n   - Returns MarkForReprocessResult with counts\n\n2. On success (count > 0):\n   - Publishes PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent\n   - Event includes: markedCount and triggerSource=\"api\"\n\n3. Response Structure:\n   ResultDTO<MarkForReprocessResponse> {\n     markedCount: int,\n     failedBatches: int,\n     failedCount: int,\n     timeCostMs: long,\n     status: \"SUCCESS\" | \"PARTIAL_SUCCESS\" | \"FAILED\",\n     message: String\n   }\n\n4. Error Handling:\n   - Returns ResultDTO.error() on exceptions\n   - Includes DEFAULT_ERROR_CODE + error message\n```\n\n### 7. **MarkForReprocess Pattern Details**\n\n**MarkForReprocessResult** (internal DTO):\n```java\n@Data @Builder\npublic class MarkForReprocessResult {\n    int updatedCount;          // Entities successfully marked\n    int failedBatches;         // Number of batch failures\n    int failedCount;           // Total entities failed in batches\n}\n```\n\n**MarkForReprocessResponse** (HTTP response):\n```java\n@Data @Builder\npublic class MarkForReprocessResponse {\n    int markedCount;           // Same as updatedCount\n    int failedBatches;\n    int failedCount;